Maitripala Senanayake and his "SLFP" as the true and legal SLFP. The developments come as a shock to Sirimavo's "SLFP". The dogmatic Sirimavo threatens to launch her own party but her supporters have already realised that by spliting the SLFP vote, neither Maitripala or Sirimavo can hope to compete with the far more united UNP. For the sake of the parties future, Sirimavo agreed to support Maitripala in the race.

Maitripala also realised the problem with splitting the SLFP vote and thus accepted Sirimavo's support. But just getting her support is not enough, the SLFP must be reunited to compete. He thus reinstated Sirimavo's membership and in hopes to placate the Left, restored Sirimavo's leadership over the SLFP though now she will be more carefull in critisising him and his Nationalists.
